cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.EM 

The paper discusses the use of computational memory, which is a topic that falls under the emerging technologies (cs.ET) category. The use of phase change memory devices for computation also falls under the category of architecture (cs.AR) and nanoscale devices and systems (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the potential for massively-parallel computing systems, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of conductance states in memory devices, which falls under the category of electromagnetics (cs.EM).
